  "text": "Using the PubMed, Cochrane, and ScienceDirect databases, [CITATION_1] determined that XLIF failed to provide adequate indirect decompression of central and lateral recess stenosis (e.g. decompression for disc disease, spinal stenosis, spondylolisthesis, and degenerative scoliosis) [ Table 1 ]. [CITATION_2] Indeed, in the 20 publications they reviewed involving 1080 patients, the efficacy of XLIF for decompressing stenosis was \"low\", and \"inconsistent\". ey further concluded: \"Most studies are limited by study design, sample size, and potential conflicts of interest. \"",
